```

### Accessing Current Theme in JavaScript

```tsx
import { useTheme } from '../hooks/useTheme';

function ComponentWithLogic() {
  const { effectiveTheme, theme } = useTheme();

  // Use effectiveTheme (resolves "auto" to actual theme)
  if (effectiveTheme === 'light') {
    // Light-specific logic
  }

  // Use theme (includes "auto" option)
  if (theme === 'auto') {
    // Auto theme selected
  }
}
```

## Performance Considerations

- **CSS Variables**: Minimal performance impact (native browser feature)
- **Theme Switching**: Smooth 200ms transitions
- **No Re-renders**: Theme changes update CSS only, components don't re-render
- **Monaco Registration**: Themes registered once on mount, not on every change

## Accessibility

- **Contrast Ratios**: All themes meet WCAG AA minimum contrast requirements
- **Focus States**: All themes define clear focus states (`focus:ring-blue-500` maps to accent)
- **System Preference**: Auto theme respects user's OS accessibility settings

